00:03:23.630 --> 00:03:25.290
the top level screens.

00:03:25.290 --> 00:03:28.510
So personally I think people
should always take advantage

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:30.210
of the branding piece of this.

00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:32.690
Not only because it tells the
user which application they're

00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:34.340
in when they're using it.

00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:37.230
But also, if they love the app,
they're going to start to

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:40.540
identify that branding with
your application.

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:42.330
Next time they're flicking
through their home screen, or

00:03:42.330 --> 00:03:46.490
in their all apps list, they'll
see that icon there.

00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:48.530
And they'll be, hey, I haven't
used that app in a while.

00:03:48.530 --> 00:03:49.680
And I really, really
like that app.

00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:50.990
And they'll come back to it.

00:03:50.990 --> 00:03:52.870
So I think this it's
really important.

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:55.030
Sometimes I see people do custom
implementations or a

00:03:55.030 --> 00:03:56.870
custom kind of action
bar, but they don't

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:57.970
include that branding.

00:03:57.970 --> 00:04:01.240
Personally, I feel very strongly
that it's important.

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:03.880
NICK: One variation on that I'd
like to mention here is

00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:06.460
that, quite commonly your
application might have a

00:04:06.460 --> 00:04:08.330
single accent color,
which you strongly

00:04:08.330 --> 00:04:09.930
associate with that brand.

00:04:09.930 --> 00:04:10.840
So [INAUDIBLE]

00:04:10.840 --> 00:04:13.580
might be pink, for example,
and so forth.

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:16.540
So there's also the opportunity
to take that

00:04:16.540 --> 00:04:19.029
accent color as your action
bar color all together.

00:04:19.029 --> 00:04:22.019
And in that case, I think it
works really, really nicely to

00:04:22.019 --> 00:04:24.515
have a differentiated logo
from your app icon.

00:04:24.515 --> 00:04:28.510
So it's entirely plausible
absolutely encouraged to have

00:04:28.510 --> 00:04:31.030
a different launcher icon that
you might have in the launch

00:04:31.030 --> 00:04:34.200
tray than the icon which appears
in the top left of the

00:04:34.200 --> 00:04:34.880
action bar.

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:36.610
So you might go for
an inverted color.

00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:40.510
Or maybe a single white
simplified version of your

00:04:40.510 --> 00:04:43.670
icon, and then use the branding
color as the actual

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:46.160
background of the action bar,
rather than having it compete

00:04:46.160 --> 00:04:48.100
with the same color.

00:04:48.100 --> 00:04:50.740
ROMAN: As long as the core icon
itself is the same, as

00:04:50.740 --> 00:04:53.770
long as the shapes and the forms
are really kind of the

00:04:53.770 --> 00:04:55.700
same thing as the launcher
icon, you can

00:04:55.700 --> 00:04:56.550
definitely do that.

00:04:56.550 --> 00:04:58.810
ADAM: And of course, the YouTube
app does this, with

00:04:58.810 --> 00:05:01.910
its launcher icon being
different to the action bar

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:03.280
app icon up there.

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:05.850
ROMAN: And actually, I think
they use a logo, as well.

00:05:05.850 --> 00:05:09.120
So you don't necessarily have
to use an icon there if you

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:11.550
have enough horizontal space
available where you don't need

00:05:11.550 --> 00:05:13.500
other items, like
view controls.

00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:15.840
You can absolutely show
a wider version.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:19.270
For developers, that's called
the Android colon logo for the

00:05:19.270 --> 00:05:20.690
action bar.

00:05:20.690 --> 00:05:22.970
But both the icon and the
logo, those should be

00:05:22.970 --> 00:05:24.545
sufficient to convey
the branding.

00:05:24.545 --> 00:05:25.640
NICK: And it works
really well.

00:05:25.640 --> 00:05:28.180
Say you have one natural
homepage, like a newsfeed, or

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:29.990
[INAUDIBLE], which is the
natural home of the content,

00:05:29.990 --> 00:05:31.880
you might want to provide
greater branding.

00:05:31.880 --> 00:05:34.770
Like say a larger logo, which
takes up more width.

00:05:34.770 --> 00:05:36.970
And then on subsequent pages,
you might want to cut that

00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:40.350
back down to a square aspect
ratio icon, which will give

00:05:40.350 --> 00:05:43.030
you more room to display
some title

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:44.730
information or view control.

00:05:44.730 --> 00:05:47.423
ADAM: Exactly, and that segues
perfectly into the second part

00:05:47.423 --> 00:05:49.475
of the action bar, which
is the control.

00:05:49.475 --> 00:05:52.100
It can be used for navigation,
something like a spinner.

00:05:52.100 --> 00:05:55.490
But also as Nick mentioned, it
can be used for a title of the

00:05:55.490 --> 00:05:56.740
particular screen, as well.

00:05:59.180 --> 00:06:01.440
ROMAN: The view control
also encompasses tabs.

00:06:01.440 --> 00:06:03.910
So in some cases, especially
in phones--

00:06:03.910 --> 00:06:06.150
and we'll talk about this
in a bit-- but tabs

00:06:06.150 --> 00:06:07.020
can go in that area.

00:06:07.020 --> 00:06:09.470
But in some cases they actually
drop into a second

00:06:09.470 --> 00:06:13.350
lower area, below that action
bars, as a stacked version.

00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:17.080
But tabs, spinner, and title,
we consider those view

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:20.630
controls, things that let you
see information about the

00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:23.540
current context, the current
screen, as well as potentially

00:06:23.540 --> 00:06:24.180
tweak things.

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:30.450
Like change perspective, or the
label, or something that

00:06:30.450 --> 00:06:31.700
you're looking at.

00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:35.370
ADAM: And then, as you
mentioned, on right side

00:06:35.370 --> 00:06:36.150
you've got your actions.

00:06:36.150 --> 00:06:37.670
So you've got your action
buttons there.

00:06:37.670 --> 00:06:41.220
In this case, there's a search
and a record video action,

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:43.430
followed by what we call the
action overflow menu.

00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:46.520
So this is where less frequently
used actions can be

00:06:46.520 --> 00:06:49.670
collapsed into an overflow menu
that's not always visible

00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:50.560
on the screen.

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:52.840
ROMAN: And very importantly for
the overflow, there are

00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:54.880
also some platform conventions
on what things

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:56.350
should always go there.

00:06:56.350 --> 00:07:00.140
So if you have application
settings, as well as Help and

00:07:00.140 --> 00:07:02.830
About, Terms of Service, things
like that should go in

00:07:02.830 --> 00:07:03.200
the overflow.

00:07:03.200 --> 00:07:05.660
You shouldn't make those
immediately on screen, unless

00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:08.770
something like Settings is the
number one use case for your

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:11.890
app, life if everybody is just
tweaking the settings.

00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:16.040
But I'd say again, 99% of the
cases overflow should contain

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:17.290
settings as well.

00:07:19.490 --> 00:07:21.020
ADAM: Moving along.

00:07:21.020 --> 00:07:22.675
NICK: Is it worth mentioning
about the overflow, then--

00:07:22.675 --> 00:07:24.070
sorry, just before
you do move on.

00:07:24.070 --> 00:07:24.980
ADAM: No, go for it.

00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:27.490
NICK: If we're talking about the
case of devices which have

00:07:27.490 --> 00:07:32.220
a physical menu button, then
the overflow button won't

00:07:32.220 --> 00:07:33.900
necessary display.

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:36.140
Because you're going to rely on
that physical affordance,

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:37.841
rather than the onscreen
affordance.

00:07:37.841 --> 00:07:38.710
ADAM: Yep, good point.

00:07:38.710 --> 00:07:40.950
And I think we have a screen
shot later on to

00:07:40.950 --> 00:07:41.810
show how that works.

00:07:41.810 --> 00:07:43.034
NICK: Oh, jumping the gun.

00:07:43.034 --> 00:07:43.850
Sorry.

00:07:43.850 --> 00:07:45.650
ADAM: No worries.

00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:48.250
So the other nice thing about
the action bar is it's very

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:50.750
good at adapting to different
screen sizes, rotations,

00:07:50.750 --> 00:07:52.370
actually the width
of the screen.

00:07:52.370 --> 00:07:54.040
It's very, very good at
adapting to that.

00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:56.530
So it does a few things to help
with the variation in

00:07:56.530 --> 00:07:58.120
screen sizes.

00:07:58.120 --> 00:08:00.870
And actually, I think it's
the next slide--

00:08:00.870 --> 00:08:03.442
one particular thing that you
can do is engage this mode

00:08:03.442 --> 00:08:06.130
called medical split
action bar mode.

00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:10.060
And actually, from a developer
standpoint, it's a flag called

00:08:10.060 --> 00:08:11.290
split action bar when narrow.

00:08:11.290 --> 00:08:14.750
So it says, when the screen with
gets down to a certain

00:08:14.750 --> 00:08:16.740
point, we're going to
go into this split

00:08:16.740 --> 00:08:18.470
action bar mode instead.

00:08:18.470 --> 00:08:21.380
So in split action bar mode,
you've got three potential

00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:23.030
different bars that
you can have here.

00:08:23.030 --> 00:08:25.210
You've got the main action
bar at the top.

00:08:25.210 --> 00:08:27.360
You've got the top bar, which
Roman was talking about

00:08:27.360 --> 00:08:28.670
before, is where the tabs could

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:30.560
potentially fall down to.

00:08:30.560 --> 00:08:32.240
And then at the bottom of the
screen you've got the bottom

00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:36.400
bar, very creatively named here,
the bottom bar, top bar.

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:39.820
And you'll see that in the
bottom bar you've got the

00:08:39.820 --> 00:08:42.620
action items, which have now
moved down there, along with

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:45.600
trailing off into the overflow
menu, rather than being at the

00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:48.230
top right there, in the
main action bar.

00:08:48.230 --> 00:08:49.960
ROMAN: A couple more points
on the screen.

00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:53.890
You'll notice that the concept
of navigation versus action,

00:08:53.890 --> 00:08:55.940
the separation of the two,
is still in play.

00:08:55.940 --> 00:08:57.515
Except that spatially it's
no longer horizontal.

00:08:57.515 --> 00:08:58.860
It's purely vertical.

00:08:58.860 --> 00:09:01.770
At the top you have all of your
navigational affordances

00:09:01.770 --> 00:09:02.420
and elements.

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:05.690
And at the very bottom you
have your actions.

00:09:05.690 --> 00:09:08.280
So that pattern is still
kept in check.

00:09:08.280 --> 00:09:09.600
The other thing I want to
mention was actually on the

00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:11.170
previous screen.

00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:15.560
Not only is the scalability, the
stretchiness of the action

00:09:15.560 --> 00:09:17.810
bar important on different
devices, but you'll also

00:09:17.810 --> 00:09:20.430
notice that on tablets the
action bar is actually

00:09:20.430 --> 00:09:21.540
slightly taller.

00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:24.450
The app icon is displayed
slightly larger.

00:09:24.450 --> 00:09:27.410
And the action bar buttons
are slightly wider.

00:09:27.410 --> 00:09:30.020
So an action bar button
on the a may be

00:09:30.020 --> 00:09:31.300
something like 56 dps.

00:09:31.300 --> 00:09:31.710
Wide.

00:09:31.710 --> 00:09:34.430
On a tablet, I think
it's about 64 dps.

00:09:34.430 --> 00:09:37.650
And the action bar height, I
think it's something like 48.

00:09:37.650 --> 00:09:39.990
And then on tablets it's 56,
or something like that.

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:43.260
But again, this stuff
may change.

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:45.800
So just using the standard
action bar gives you

00:09:45.800 --> 00:09:47.710
all this for free.

00:09:47.710 --> 00:09:50.020
ADAM: And if potentially some
huge tablet comes out in the

00:09:50.020 --> 00:09:52.270
future, or something like that,
the action bar may have

00:09:52.270 --> 00:09:54.160
a different size again, a
different way of formatting.

00:09:54.160 --> 00:09:56.050
But as long as you stick to
using action bar, your

00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:59.100
application should still look
and display fine here.

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.100
ROMAN: One more [INAUDIBLE].

