00:28:57.696 --> 00:29:01.300
That comes for free from the
system to use the native

00:29:01.300 --> 00:29:02.160
action bar.

00:29:02.160 --> 00:29:03.780
ROMAN: And lastly,
Done and Discard.

00:29:03.780 --> 00:29:05.440
This is something that's
not yet documented.

00:29:05.440 --> 00:29:07.500
I think we'll probably be
documenting it in the future.

00:29:07.500 --> 00:29:10.650
But as an alternative, if you
have a really, really simple

00:29:10.650 --> 00:29:16.130
screen, like for example like
just a single edit screen, or

00:29:16.130 --> 00:29:18.980
something, and you really only
have two things you can do--

00:29:18.980 --> 00:29:21.090
either Save or Cancel--

00:29:21.090 --> 00:29:22.310
and you don't want to
use a dialogue.

00:29:22.310 --> 00:29:24.690
Because generally, you want
to avoid dialogues.

00:29:24.690 --> 00:29:28.550
You want to avoid the extra
burden on the user to think

00:29:28.550 --> 00:29:32.180
about what else is around
the screen.

00:29:32.180 --> 00:29:35.840
You can use the done slash
discard pattern, where instead

00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:38.580
of an action bar, instead of
the Up button, instead of a

00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:41.080
title and overflow,
you just show two

00:29:41.080 --> 00:29:42.350
actions, Done and Discard.

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.670
And there's, again positive
button on the right, negative

00:29:44.670 --> 00:29:45.510
but on the left.

00:29:45.510 --> 00:29:48.270
Alternatively, if discarding is
not really that common, or

00:29:48.270 --> 00:29:50.530
if you have other actions you
need to show, you can just

00:29:50.530 --> 00:29:53.230
show Done in the top left,
which takes the

00:29:53.230 --> 00:29:55.540
place of the Up button.

00:29:55.540 --> 00:29:58.760
And that's like the same thing
as saying, if I press this I

00:29:58.760 --> 00:30:02.440
have the added confidence that
when I go up, or when I leave

00:30:02.440 --> 00:30:04.890
this context, I'm actually
persisting

00:30:04.890 --> 00:30:06.460
my content, my changes.

00:30:06.460 --> 00:30:08.540
So that's just an alternative
that you can use for very

00:30:08.540 --> 00:30:10.190
simple screens.

